SIMPLE: bondage
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bondage
<hw>Bond"age</hw> <pr>(-⟦asl⟧j)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>bondagium</ets>. See <er>Bond</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being bound; condition of being under
restraint; restraint of personal liberty by compulsion; involuntary
servitude; slavery; captivity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The King, when he designed you for my guard,⟦br⟧
Resolved he would not make my <qex>bondage</qex> hard.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Obligation; tie of duty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He must resolve by no means to be . . . brought under the
<qex>bondage</qex> of observing oaths.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Old Eng. Law)</fld> <def>Villenage; tenure of land
on condition of doing the meanest services for the owner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Thralldom; bond service; imprisonment.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bondager</ent>⟦br⟧
